author: Magic Beans🐿️
text: My 2022 tests ahead are MRI, EEG, colonoscopy (number 3), Fibroscan for liver, lung spirometry. I stayed in Calgary to go to these. I want to leave and start over with a fresh mind and heart in Sylvan Lake with my dogs. I hope leaving will help me find people I can call friends.

author: Magic Beans🐿️
text: I've fallen down the stairs, I've fallen outside and broke my leg last year. I fall in the house. I can't breathe worth shit but somehow my doctor will not supply a handicap parking sticker for my truck or anyone who drives me to appointments. I hate bullshit.

author: Magic Beans🐿️
text: During the cardiac test though, some useful data came from wires tracking my vitals. When I got back to my doctors, he had not reviewed the testing and refused to ever look at the data that was showing stuff he doesn't know. I am too smart for this bullshit.

author: Magic Beans🐿️
text: If they can't take time to know their patients but order tests that cost the taxpayer (and me) thousands of dollars, I most often refuse now. I've had it. They spent an estimated $50,000 on cardiac testing for me. I have a strong heart. There was no reason for the test.

author: Magic Beans🐿️
text: The EEG was to look for a cause for seizures but the test is specifically to epilepsy. He didn't care that I was mugged or have 30 concussions and a brain injury. Blindly he trudges ahead. I don't want to go anymore. The MRI he ordered doesn't show anything either.

author: Magic Beans🐿️
text: Going to another doctor or not going doesn't mean I gave up. It just means I don't feel like wasting any more time on tests for THEM to know whats wrong with me. I have a lot of concussions for one thing and CTE but THEY look for other illness instead. Waste of time.

author: Magic Beans🐿️
text: When you first start getting sick, you search everywhere for answers. At some point you reach acceptance and understand, there is no cure for somethings and the only thing you can do is try to maximize your health and happiness on the way down. I'm there for a couple years now.

author: Magic Beans🐿️
text: I stayed in Calgary because of all the health specialists I have to visit this year. My EEG for the brain cancelled this week and I'm almost ready to just cancel them all. I accept my fate. Its not like I go to them to find a cure. I know whats wrong, why bother?
